WEBVTT

00:01.711 --> 00:03.295
[percussion playing]

00:03.295 --> 00:04.964
[whistle blows]

00:04.964 --> 00:06.966
[cheering continues]

00:08.259 --> 00:10.261
♪ ♪

00:13.055 --> 00:15.307
[announcer] Welcome
to the 35th annual

00:15.307 --> 00:18.936
Carp Fourth of July parade!

00:18.936 --> 00:22.898
Y'all better not miss
the Metal Stampede, coming soon!

00:22.898 --> 00:25.109
Let's give it up for

00:25.109 --> 00:27.778
the Samuel Maverick High School
marching band!

00:27.778 --> 00:30.281
- [cheering]
- Oh.

00:30.281 --> 00:31.574
Look, there's Bishop.

00:31.574 --> 00:33.117
[Natalie] Oh, and, Diggins.

00:33.117 --> 00:35.453
- Maybe you could work him
for intel.
- Hey.

00:38.205 --> 00:39.623
- Hi.
- Ladies.

00:39.623 --> 00:40.916
[Natalie] No. No ladies.

00:40.916 --> 00:42.501
It's been nine days, Diggins.

00:42.501 --> 00:44.128
Have you not heard anything
from the judges?

00:44.128 --> 00:46.422
Patience, grasshopper.
Patience.

00:46.422 --> 00:48.716
[announcer] Mainstreet Wireless
wishes you a safe

00:48.716 --> 00:50.593
and happy Fourth.

00:50.593 --> 00:53.179
- And to think,
that could've been you.
- Mm.

00:53.179 --> 00:55.181
Why don't you wave goodbye to
the Ghost of Shittier Jobs Past,

00:55.181 --> 00:57.308
- Heather.
- [Heather] Yeah?
Which finger should I use?

00:57.308 --> 00:59.393
- [chuckles]
- [announcer] And how 'bout them

00:59.393 --> 01:01.520
tri-county beauty queens, huh?

01:01.520 --> 01:02.938
Oh. Check out Leela.

01:02.938 --> 01:05.524
She looks beautiful.

01:06.650 --> 01:08.652
[Diggins] She's into you.

01:08.652 --> 01:10.070
♪ ♪

01:10.070 --> 01:11.822
[Bishop] Shut up.

01:13.657 --> 01:15.659
All right, later, losers.

01:17.036 --> 01:18.037
[announcer] Oh, my!

01:18.037 --> 01:19.455
It's Arnie,

01:19.455 --> 01:21.874
the most rootin'-tootin'
Fighting Armadillo.

01:21.874 --> 01:23.542
Uh, guys?

01:28.047 --> 01:30.466
I mean, it's got to be
a clue, right?

01:30.466 --> 01:32.468
♪ ♪

01:36.597 --> 01:38.307
[grunting, laughing]

01:38.307 --> 01:40.226
- There you go.
- Seriously?

01:40.226 --> 01:42.144
We just got
our first clue in weeks,

01:42.144 --> 01:43.479
and now you guys want
to recapture

01:43.479 --> 01:46.023
your sense of childhood joy?

01:46.023 --> 01:47.691
It's a national holiday, Nat.

01:47.691 --> 01:49.360
Slacking off is patriotic.

01:49.360 --> 01:51.028
[groans]

01:51.028 --> 01:53.364
I'm gonna go find Shawna.

01:53.364 --> 01:55.574
She says the marching band
has a musical float.

01:55.574 --> 01:57.201
Maybe that's supposed
to be the key?

01:57.201 --> 01:59.119
Good luck, Sherlock.

01:59.119 --> 02:01.914
[announcer speaking in distance]

02:01.914 --> 02:03.749
Do you remember
when we were kids

02:03.749 --> 02:05.167
and my mom used to say

02:05.167 --> 02:06.710
if you swung high enough,

02:06.710 --> 02:08.671
you could kick the clouds
around with a toe?

02:08.671 --> 02:11.215
I remember she said
that the Man in the Moon

02:11.215 --> 02:12.967
was a kid who face-planted

02:12.967 --> 02:14.593
- in a pile of wet concrete.
- [laughs]

02:14.593 --> 02:16.887
One time I asked her
why it got bigger and smaller,

02:16.887 --> 02:18.305
and she said, "Construction."

02:18.305 --> 02:21.392
So for years, I thought
there was an astronaut

02:21.392 --> 02:22.893
doing repair work on the Moon.

02:22.893 --> 02:25.020
You know?

02:25.020 --> 02:26.897
[exhales]

02:26.897 --> 02:28.399
If I ever start a band,

02:28.399 --> 02:30.359
I'm definitely naming it
Construction Moon Work.

02:30.359 --> 02:31.318
Ooh!

02:33.070 --> 02:34.321
Count me in as a groupie.

02:34.321 --> 02:35.698
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

02:35.698 --> 02:37.616
Does that mean
I can count on you

02:37.616 --> 02:39.034
to throw your bra onstage?

02:39.034 --> 02:41.078
Depends.

02:41.078 --> 02:43.873
How hot's the bass player?

02:43.873 --> 02:45.541
You tell me.

02:46.584 --> 02:48.294
You're looking at him.

02:48.294 --> 02:51.505
[footsteps approaching]

02:51.505 --> 02:53.465
Is it our turn yet?

02:53.465 --> 02:55.509
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
She's-she's all yours.

02:56.719 --> 02:58.095
[Heather grunts]

02:58.095 --> 02:59.889
[Heather] There you go.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.606
Where'd you get that tattoo
on your hand?

03:08.606 --> 03:11.734
There's more behind the
locksmith's if you want one.

03:14.153 --> 03:16.155
♪ ♪

03:23.579 --> 03:25.539
[Heather] "Spurlock Farm."

03:25.539 --> 03:26.999
"Breaking and entering."

03:26.999 --> 03:28.375
"Tomorrow."

03:30.377 --> 03:31.503
"10:00 p.m."

03:32.630 --> 03:33.631
Jesus.

03:33.631 --> 03:37.009
I remember John Davis Hale.

03:37.009 --> 03:38.886
And what happened
at Spurlock's farm.

03:43.724 --> 03:45.726
[insects trilling]

03:54.068 --> 03:55.986
[Ray] By the time individual
challenges rolled around...

03:55.986 --> 03:58.447
You're not even gonna spank me?

03:58.447 --> 03:59.865
[emcee] Very funny.

03:59.865 --> 04:01.867
[Ray] ...John Davis was
the favorite to win.

04:04.328 --> 04:06.872
Place even a toe outside
before morning

04:06.872 --> 04:08.666
and you're out.

04:08.666 --> 04:10.334
See you in the morning.

04:10.334 --> 04:13.462
[Ray] John Davis knew
he was in for snakes.

04:15.631 --> 04:18.842
Since freshman year,
he'd been sure to tell everyone

04:18.842 --> 04:21.011
how scared he was of snakes.

04:21.011 --> 04:23.639
[hissing]

04:23.639 --> 04:26.475
[Ray] And that's why
John Davis Hale was in the lead.

04:28.143 --> 04:30.688
Who's ready to party?

04:30.688 --> 04:32.773
[Ray] He'd been lying
since freshman year

04:32.773 --> 04:34.692
just to get ahead in the game.

04:37.277 --> 04:40.572
John Davis grew up
in a 200-year-old farmhouse

04:40.572 --> 04:42.074
in deep backcountry.

04:42.074 --> 04:43.701
There were garter snakes
in the basement

04:43.701 --> 04:45.744
- and black rat snakes
in the attic.
- [laughs]

04:45.744 --> 04:47.579
[John Davis] What an idiot.

04:47.579 --> 04:49.665
[Ray] Come wintertime, they'd
shimmy down into the pipes,

04:49.665 --> 04:51.250
and he used to collect
their skins

04:51.250 --> 04:54.336
and hang 'em on the wall
for decoration at Halloween.

04:57.131 --> 04:58.966
- [fireworks going off]
- [people exclaiming]

04:58.966 --> 05:00.676
[laughs]

05:00.676 --> 05:02.302
[yelping]

05:05.264 --> 05:07.349
[John Davis] Come on, Verizon.

05:07.349 --> 05:09.143
[Ray] You see, truth is,

05:09.143 --> 05:11.687
he didn't give a fuck
about snakes.

05:13.522 --> 05:15.774
[video resumes playing]

05:17.693 --> 05:19.528
[skittering]

05:22.698 --> 05:24.658
[animal chittering]

05:33.292 --> 05:36.420
[Ray] There was only one thing
John Davis was afraid of.

05:39.339 --> 05:41.383
He was afraid of bats.

05:41.383 --> 05:42.593
[squeaks]

05:42.593 --> 05:44.887
[screaming]

05:44.887 --> 05:47.222
Oh, God! Oh, God!

05:49.975 --> 05:51.769
[squeaking, chittering]

05:51.769 --> 05:54.188
[groans]

05:54.188 --> 05:56.482
[groaning]
Oh, fuck.

05:59.151 --> 06:00.486
[groans]

06:04.073 --> 06:05.199
[exhales]

06:05.199 --> 06:07.242
[panting, chuckling]

06:08.994 --> 06:10.704
[screams]

06:10.704 --> 06:13.040
[squelching sound]

06:13.040 --> 06:15.042
♪ ♪

06:19.004 --> 06:20.672
[Ray] They found his guts

06:20.672 --> 06:22.674
coiled around some
of the old machinery.

06:22.674 --> 06:23.717
♪ Yeah...

06:23.717 --> 06:27.846
And absolutely covered
in bat shit.

06:27.846 --> 06:29.306
♪ Here we go again...

06:29.306 --> 06:31.016
That's... that's bullshit.

06:31.016 --> 06:32.935
How did the judges know
that he was scared of bats?

06:32.935 --> 06:33.936
That doesn't make any sense.

06:33.936 --> 06:35.104
They didn't.

06:35.104 --> 06:37.064
It was bad luck.

06:37.064 --> 06:38.816
- [ghostly noises]
- [Tyler] What are you
talking about?

06:38.816 --> 06:40.609
Davis was after
Spurlock's stash.

06:40.609 --> 06:42.069
Truck told me he-he's got money

06:42.069 --> 06:43.362
buried all over
the fucking farm.

06:43.362 --> 06:44.947
Drums full of it.

06:44.947 --> 06:46.573
Near his grow house.

06:46.573 --> 06:48.784
Look, Spurlock caught Davis,

06:48.784 --> 06:50.160
plugged him, and then faked

06:50.160 --> 06:51.995
the fucking accident.

06:51.995 --> 06:53.413
He's a fucking criminal.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.790
[Adam] Hale wasn't stealing.

06:54.790 --> 06:56.291
He was bagman.
He stored his money

06:56.291 --> 06:57.668
on Spurlock's farm
because of the booby trap.

06:57.668 --> 06:58.794
Bagman?

06:58.794 --> 07:00.045
Keeper of the pot.

07:00.045 --> 07:01.755
I thought that was
the collector's job.

07:01.755 --> 07:03.382
Nah. We're just the muscle.

07:03.382 --> 07:04.842
Bagman gets in touch,

07:04.842 --> 07:07.136
tells us where
to drop off the money

07:07.136 --> 07:08.679
and when.

07:08.679 --> 07:10.305
I can't believe no one knows
who the bagman is.

07:10.305 --> 07:12.224
Would you want someone knowing
you're sitting

07:12.224 --> 07:13.517
on all that money?

07:13.517 --> 07:15.269
[Sarah]
Look at what happened last year.

07:15.269 --> 07:17.104
Yeah. 30K, gone.

07:17.104 --> 07:18.397
Just like that.

07:18.397 --> 07:20.566
We should forget about
the challenge tomorrow.

07:20.566 --> 07:22.359
Go for the real payload.

07:22.359 --> 07:24.069
I mean, seriously,

07:24.069 --> 07:25.904
if Spurlock has money
actually buried...

07:25.904 --> 07:27.239
That's a great idea.

07:27.239 --> 07:28.615
- [Ruby Anne laughs]
- How about I stand guard

07:28.615 --> 07:31.994
and you shovel out 3,000 acres?

07:31.994 --> 07:33.537
[laughter]

07:33.537 --> 07:35.998
I wasn't talking about a shovel,
you dick.

07:35.998 --> 07:37.708
The game's changing, you guys.
I'm serious.

07:37.708 --> 07:40.002
It was one thing
before the cops knew.

07:40.002 --> 07:42.337
Now half the game is just trying
to avoid 'em.

07:42.337 --> 07:43.714
Or not.

07:43.714 --> 07:45.340
Sorry.

07:45.340 --> 07:47.217
[Tyler] Yeah.
How are things with Cortez

07:47.217 --> 07:49.011
down at the station?
You getting a little cozy?

07:49.011 --> 07:50.762
- [Ruby Anne] Ooh!
- Yeah.

07:50.762 --> 07:53.265
Forty hours and handcuffs
will do that to you, dipshit.

07:53.265 --> 07:56.143
[Ray] Just imagine
if Cortez got ahold

07:56.143 --> 07:58.645
- of El Chapo over here.
- [laughter]

07:58.645 --> 08:00.981
Our big businessman'd
be looking at federal.

08:00.981 --> 08:02.024
- [chuckling]
- That's not fucking funny.

08:02.024 --> 08:03.108
[Ray] Relax.

08:03.108 --> 08:04.526
Pretty face like that,

08:04.526 --> 08:06.028
you're gonna be making
a lot of new friends.

08:06.028 --> 08:07.404
[laughter]

08:10.157 --> 08:11.283
[Williams] So, what'd you get
from Sarah Miller?

08:11.283 --> 08:12.868
Well, Sarah and her friends

08:12.868 --> 08:14.661
thought that they were just
going to a party at the granary.

08:14.661 --> 08:16.663
And when they got there,
they realized

08:16.663 --> 08:19.416
that the seniors had already
set up a challenge.

08:19.416 --> 08:22.336
Well, did she confirm
what Myra said about the judges?

08:22.336 --> 08:24.087
Mm.
Whoever the current judges are,

08:24.087 --> 08:25.464
they're always hand-picked
in secret

08:25.464 --> 08:27.424
by the previous year's judges.

08:27.424 --> 08:30.219
So those in charge this year
know who ran point last summer.

08:30.219 --> 08:32.095
- Yeah, and vice versa.
- [Cortez] Those four kids.

08:32.095 --> 08:35.140
All we have to do is nab
one of 'em, and we got 'em all.

08:35.140 --> 08:36.975
Last year's judges...

08:36.975 --> 08:39.102
they got two bodies
on their conscience.

08:40.771 --> 08:42.272
Yeah, they do.

08:42.272 --> 08:43.357
[Williams] Can't be too easy,

08:43.357 --> 08:44.816
carrying that kind
of weight around.

08:44.816 --> 08:46.693
It's got to be showing.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.445
Williams, I want you
to go to the church

08:48.445 --> 08:50.030
and talk to Reverend Redd.

08:50.030 --> 08:51.406
He knows this town.

08:51.406 --> 08:53.742
He knows who's in pain,
he knows who's in trouble.

08:53.742 --> 08:54.993
Now go.

08:57.079 --> 09:00.374
And you... I want you
to make nice with Sarah Miller,

09:00.374 --> 09:02.709
now that she's got to do
her community service here.

09:02.709 --> 09:04.544
She's not gonna give me
any more information.

09:04.544 --> 09:06.046
She knows
we don't know jack shit.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.756
So I want you
to get close to her.

09:07.756 --> 09:08.757
I want you to warm her up.

09:08.757 --> 09:09.800
You know, connect with her.

09:09.800 --> 09:10.968
Go.

09:13.011 --> 09:15.013
[birds singing]

09:17.266 --> 09:19.309
[♪ Hazel English: "Wake Up!"]

09:19.309 --> 09:21.270
[whinnies]

09:22.271 --> 09:24.439
♪ Can you wake ♪

09:24.439 --> 09:26.316
♪ From this dream ♪

09:26.316 --> 09:29.569
♪ That they told you
to believe ♪

09:29.569 --> 09:31.029
♪ So you ♪

09:31.029 --> 09:33.740
♪ Can finally be free ♪

09:33.740 --> 09:35.826
♪ ♪

09:35.826 --> 09:37.286
- ♪ Do you trust...
- [bleats]

09:37.286 --> 09:38.787
[brakes screech]

09:38.787 --> 09:41.873
- [bleats]
- ♪ Is it just another scheme? ♪

09:41.873 --> 09:43.667
♪ Get you ♪

09:43.667 --> 09:45.043
♪ To buy ♪

09:45.043 --> 09:46.461
♪ All of the things ♪♪

09:46.461 --> 09:47.713
[engine shuts off]

09:47.713 --> 09:50.882
Okay. The chicken coop is
right behind the house.

09:50.882 --> 09:52.551
You just got to keep it
well locked up,

09:52.551 --> 09:55.804
- because, uh...
- [both laugh]

09:55.804 --> 09:57.264
...the coyotes might get 'em,
you know.

09:57.264 --> 09:59.266
- Yeah.
- So...

09:59.266 --> 10:01.935
And, uh, that fence
way out there?

10:01.935 --> 10:03.145
Yeah.

10:03.145 --> 10:05.397
[Anne] You want to stay
downhill of that.

10:05.397 --> 10:07.149
The fence is there for a reason.

10:07.149 --> 10:09.985
Some animals never get
the wild out of 'em.

10:09.985 --> 10:11.236
[exhales]

10:11.236 --> 10:14.281
That's the upper field
and the lower field.

10:14.281 --> 10:16.575
Call that "the prairie."

10:16.575 --> 10:17.826
Pretty.

10:17.826 --> 10:20.912
And the, the stables
and the riding ring.

10:20.912 --> 10:22.748
You ride?

10:22.748 --> 10:24.207
- Horses?
- Yeah.

10:24.207 --> 10:25.584
Mm, no.

10:25.584 --> 10:26.668
Well, I got six.

10:26.668 --> 10:28.170
Four of my own,
couple of boarders.

10:28.170 --> 10:30.672
They need a lot of exercise,
and I'm gonna have to teach you.

10:30.672 --> 10:31.840
Yeah, I don't know.

10:31.840 --> 10:33.592
I can barely ride a bike.

10:33.592 --> 10:35.802
You know, I think I'd be
too scared of falling off.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.596
Really? You don’t seem the type.

10:37.596 --> 10:38.889
To get scared?

10:38.889 --> 10:40.432
To let it stop you.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.811
You didn’t even ask
if llamas bite.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.482
Llamas don’t bite.

10:50.484 --> 10:52.486
Do llamas bite?

10:52.486 --> 10:54.863
[music playing softly]

10:56.782 --> 10:58.533
[Jessica] Mm. Mm-mm, mm-mm.

10:58.533 --> 11:00.494
Mm-mm.

11:00.494 --> 11:02.871
You hate cigarettes, too, huh?

11:02.871 --> 11:04.790
[exhales]

11:06.291 --> 11:08.710
[sighs] Jimmy always hated
when I smoked.

11:08.710 --> 11:11.922
He said these things
were gonna kill me.

11:11.922 --> 11:14.341
Well, it’s never that easy,
is it? Hmm?

11:15.675 --> 11:18.678
I think Jimmy was right.

11:20.472 --> 11:24.101
You can tell me, you know.

11:24.101 --> 11:26.103
About Jimmy.

11:30.565 --> 11:33.193
You can tell me
anything you want.

11:35.237 --> 11:37.948
Remember a few years ago,

11:37.948 --> 11:40.575
when the Powerball got up to...

11:40.575 --> 11:41.993
- to a billion?
- Yeah.

11:41.993 --> 11:44.162
At the station, we put together
this pool, right?

11:44.162 --> 11:45.664
And we bought a hundred tickets,
and, well,

11:45.664 --> 11:48.125
if one of 'em hit,
we were gonna split 'em.

11:48.125 --> 11:50.377
[sighs]

11:50.377 --> 11:53.380
So we're sitting there, looking
at the numbers come up, right?

11:53.380 --> 11:54.798
Those little balls, uh...

11:54.798 --> 11:57.884
- Ping-Pong.
- They're called lotto balls.

11:57.884 --> 12:00.929
So the first one comes up,
I look at my ticket.

12:00.929 --> 12:02.556
It's a match.

12:02.556 --> 12:05.684
Second one goes up,
it's a match.

12:05.684 --> 12:07.644
Third one goes up, it's a match.

12:07.644 --> 12:10.355
- No.
- I shit you not.

12:10.355 --> 12:13.066
Fourth one goes up, a match.

12:13.066 --> 12:15.068
Everybody in that room
was silent.

12:15.068 --> 12:16.653
I mean, literally,
they're holding their breath,

12:16.653 --> 12:17.863
and I could just see 'em
thinking about

12:17.863 --> 12:20.198
all the shit they're gonna buy.

12:21.491 --> 12:24.703
Yeah. Last ball goes up.

12:24.703 --> 12:27.706
Thirty-four.
I looked down at my ticket.

12:27.706 --> 12:30.584
- I have 35.
- Ugh.

12:30.584 --> 12:33.587
I was one lousy digit away
from a billion dollars.

12:33.587 --> 12:37.799
But the thing is, I wasn't
a lousy digit from shit.

12:37.799 --> 12:39.718
There's no second place
to not winning,

12:39.718 --> 12:43.305
just like there's
no second place to not living.

12:43.305 --> 12:45.807
And that’s why I don’t talk
about Jimmy, ever.

12:45.807 --> 12:47.267
He’s gone.

12:48.310 --> 12:50.812
♪ ♪

12:52.814 --> 12:54.858
There's nothing else to say.

12:56.860 --> 12:58.445
At the end of the day,
you either have a kid

12:58.445 --> 13:00.280
that's breathing...

13:03.867 --> 13:05.452
Or you don’t.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.830
Or you don't.

13:08.830 --> 13:11.708
Hey, hey. Listen to me.

13:13.585 --> 13:16.922
Even if you stop this game

13:16.922 --> 13:20.342
and you bring it
all down for good...

13:22.344 --> 13:24.304
...it's not gonna
bring Jimmy back.

13:28.767 --> 13:31.478
Nothing’s ever gonna
bring my Jimmy back.

13:33.480 --> 13:35.857
Just like nothing's
ever gonna get your Dayna

13:35.857 --> 13:37.859
out of that wheelchair.

13:49.329 --> 13:51.414
[car door opens, closes]

13:51.414 --> 13:53.416
[car engine starts]

13:55.835 --> 13:58.838
[indistinct radio chatter]

14:00.924 --> 14:02.926
♪ ♪

14:25.949 --> 14:28.076
[Dayna] Can I help you?

14:30.954 --> 14:33.331
Hi.

14:40.755 --> 14:42.591
I was just hanging up
some flyers

14:42.591 --> 14:45.385
for the charity chili cook-off.

14:45.385 --> 14:48.263
[chuckles] Never knew
there was a house back here.

14:48.263 --> 14:50.473
If you’re the one keeps
snatching our packages,

14:50.473 --> 14:52.434
- I hope you’re enjoying
all the free mouthwash.
- Oh, no.

14:52.434 --> 14:55.103
I was, uh, just, uh,
bringing it to you.

14:55.103 --> 14:56.521
Special delivery.

14:56.521 --> 14:59.774
It’s for-for Dodge?

14:59.774 --> 15:00.775
[Dayna] It’s for me.

15:00.775 --> 15:02.527
Dayna Mason.

15:02.527 --> 15:04.362
I’m Dodge’s sister.

15:05.447 --> 15:07.115
He never told me
he had a sister.

15:07.115 --> 15:08.533
[Dayna] Don’t take it personal.

15:08.533 --> 15:10.410
One time he broke
the state record

15:10.410 --> 15:12.120
at the Legacy Rodeo series,

15:12.120 --> 15:15.582
and we didn’t find out
until we saw him on the news.

15:15.582 --> 15:17.208
Rodeo?

15:17.208 --> 15:19.628
You want me to tell him
you stopped by?

15:19.628 --> 15:21.921
Natalie.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.798
[gate closes]

15:39.439 --> 15:41.483
[grunts]

15:41.483 --> 15:43.610
- [Sarah] Goddamn it.
- Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

15:45.278 --> 15:47.989
No, stop.
Stop, stop, stop. Stop.

15:47.989 --> 15:50.033
There's a trick to this one.

15:50.033 --> 15:52.494
Here.

15:52.494 --> 15:54.204
Hmm.

15:56.247 --> 15:59.250
- I’m supposed to organize
all of these?
- Yes, ma'am.

15:59.250 --> 16:00.627
The thing they don't tell you
about police work

16:00.627 --> 16:02.504
is that it's mostly paperwork.

16:02.504 --> 16:04.631
These, these are the Does.
Those are the bodies

16:04.631 --> 16:07.258
- that show up with no ID.
- Oh, God.

16:07.258 --> 16:09.719
That's nothing. Before I came
here, I did seven years

16:09.719 --> 16:12.097
in SVU down in Dallas.

16:12.097 --> 16:14.224
I was, like, all set up
for a promotion.

16:14.224 --> 16:16.601
They were gonna give me twice
the pay, ten times the action.

16:16.601 --> 16:18.978
Everyone thought I was crazy
for transferring out here.

16:18.978 --> 16:21.189
So why did you?

16:21.189 --> 16:23.316
Because who wants ten times
of that kind of action?

16:23.316 --> 16:25.568
Fair enough.

16:25.568 --> 16:28.571
Funny enough, it wasn’t
the real kids that did me in.

16:30.573 --> 16:33.368
Real live kids meant
you have a chance

16:33.368 --> 16:36.329
at catching the person
that hurt them and busting them.

16:36.329 --> 16:38.331
It was all the photos.

16:38.331 --> 16:41.000
It was like, hundreds of them,
thousands of them.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.627
Girls mostly.

16:42.627 --> 16:44.671
Photos leaked by boys
they thought loved them.

16:44.671 --> 16:47.173
Photos of... lonely girls

16:47.173 --> 16:49.342
sharing them with online friends
that then blackmailed them

16:49.342 --> 16:51.845
- for more and more.
- Like what happened
with Abby Clark.

16:55.515 --> 16:57.058
What happened with Abby Clark?

17:00.979 --> 17:02.188
[sighs]

17:02.188 --> 17:04.816
You're a cop. Figure it out.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.487
- [Dodge] Hey, Mom.
- Hey.

17:09.487 --> 17:11.740
- [Dodge] What happened?
- [Jessica] Faucet is leaking,

17:11.740 --> 17:14.242
- and the drip
was driving me crazy.
- Mm.

17:14.242 --> 17:15.744
You hungry?

17:15.744 --> 17:18.121
[Dodge] Dot had me clean out
the grease trap last night,

17:18.121 --> 17:21.374
so I doubt I’ll be hungry
for about a month.

17:22.834 --> 17:24.461
[TV playing indistinctly]

17:27.756 --> 17:29.674
Where’s Dayna?

17:30.884 --> 17:32.635
In her room.

17:32.635 --> 17:36.055
Still giving me
the silent treatment.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.682
The sheriff came by.

17:37.682 --> 17:40.560
Well, thin walls.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.937
You know, there was a time
y'all used to tell me

17:42.937 --> 17:44.397
to go out and date.

17:44.397 --> 17:47.192
- He’s married.
- Thank God for that.

17:47.192 --> 17:49.527
Otherwise he'd be coming
around here looking for a wife.

17:53.531 --> 17:57.744
You used to hate cops.

17:57.744 --> 17:59.746
[sighs]

18:01.831 --> 18:03.625
That was before I needed one.

18:06.711 --> 18:09.964
You know I’m just trying to do
the right thing for Dayna.

18:09.964 --> 18:12.592
For all of us.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.636
But you want to change anything
in this world,

18:14.636 --> 18:16.763
then you have to have
the right kind of friends.

18:16.763 --> 18:18.765
[exhales]

18:21.184 --> 18:23.019
Except it’s never
really friendship

18:23.019 --> 18:25.021
that they’re looking for, is it?

18:34.322 --> 18:36.241
[Mary] I know about the game,
you know.

18:36.241 --> 18:38.576
Abby admitted she was going
to play when I confronted her.

18:38.576 --> 18:41.871
I checked her text messages.

18:41.871 --> 18:43.998
- She didn't lock her phone?
- I had the pass code.

18:43.998 --> 18:46.709
That was our agreement
when I bought the phone.

18:48.294 --> 18:51.589
I only checked
a handful of times.

18:51.589 --> 18:53.591
She wasn't acting like herself.

18:53.591 --> 18:56.135
She was always dodging me,
always running off with Myra,

18:56.135 --> 18:58.930
one of her friends
from the dance team.

18:58.930 --> 19:00.890
Did you see
what was on her phone?

19:00.890 --> 19:02.559
Abby said she wasn't sure
if she wanted

19:02.559 --> 19:04.435
to go through with it anymore.

19:04.435 --> 19:08.314
Jimmy was pressuring her,
saying she wouldn't regret it.

19:09.357 --> 19:11.234
You thought she was
talking about sex.

19:11.234 --> 19:13.361
But now I know that she wasn't.

19:13.361 --> 19:16.239
She swore that the challenges
weren't dangerous.

19:16.239 --> 19:18.825
[laughs]

19:18.825 --> 19:20.410
I would have locked her
in her room.

19:20.410 --> 19:21.828
I would have boarded up
her windows

19:21.828 --> 19:23.788
so she couldn’t run away.
[sniffles]

19:27.750 --> 19:30.545
We know that the games are
organized by a pair of judges.

19:30.545 --> 19:33.464
- Did she ever say anything
about them?
- I don’t care who organized it.

19:33.464 --> 19:34.841
I want to know who killed her.

19:35.884 --> 19:37.385
I'm sorry, what?

19:37.385 --> 19:39.637
[Mary] Like I told
the sheriff last year,

19:39.637 --> 19:43.933
a few weeks before...
before what happened,

19:43.933 --> 19:46.561
Abby mentioned notes.

19:46.561 --> 19:49.606
Threats left in our mailbox

19:49.606 --> 19:51.357
saying that if she didn't
quit the game,

19:51.357 --> 19:54.152
that bad things would happen.

19:54.152 --> 19:55.904
[Langley] Huh.
Do you have those notes?

19:55.904 --> 19:58.573
[Mary] No.
I didn't even see them.

19:58.573 --> 20:01.701
So, there was only one reason

20:01.701 --> 20:04.329
why she stepped
onto the highway.

20:04.329 --> 20:07.707
The threats pushed her
over the edge.

20:09.125 --> 20:11.127
[music playing softly]

20:13.046 --> 20:14.547
[knocking]

20:21.888 --> 20:23.514
- [entry bell jingles]
- Hi.

20:23.514 --> 20:25.516
Hey. Can I come in?

20:25.516 --> 20:26.726
Sure.

20:31.814 --> 20:34.025
Can I, uh, get you
a coffee or something? Or...

20:34.025 --> 20:36.402
- No, I'm okay.
- Okay.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.655
[exhales sharply]

20:38.655 --> 20:42.450
I have to say, people have done
a lot of crazy things

20:42.450 --> 20:44.786
to win Panic,
but reenrolling in school

20:44.786 --> 20:46.371
after you’ve already graduated?

20:46.371 --> 20:49.165
Well, that takes the cake,

20:49.165 --> 20:51.376
Andrew Dodge Mason.

20:51.376 --> 20:53.753
[chuckles]
You know what?

20:55.088 --> 20:58.591
Why don't we just stick
with Dodge?

21:02.178 --> 21:05.056
- How'd you find out?
- My dad's a cop.

21:05.056 --> 21:08.142
He told me to notice things
that other people don't see.

21:08.142 --> 21:09.978
Congratulations.

21:09.978 --> 21:11.729
I see you made it
to the National Rodeo Finals

21:11.729 --> 21:13.856
second year running,
saddle bronc.

21:13.856 --> 21:16.526
I didn’t know you competed.

21:16.526 --> 21:18.695
Tell me the truth.

21:18.695 --> 21:20.321
You get one chance.

21:20.321 --> 21:23.574
You lie to me,
I get you disqualified.

21:23.574 --> 21:24.867
Are you a judge?

21:24.867 --> 21:26.285
No.

21:26.285 --> 21:28.121
No, I didn’t even move here
till mid-August.

21:28.121 --> 21:29.789
Still plenty of time to plan.

21:29.789 --> 21:32.250
Sure. If last year’s

21:32.250 --> 21:34.585
judges felt like picking
a total stranger.

21:36.879 --> 21:38.464
Why are you playing?

21:42.719 --> 21:45.847
Hurricane Harvey wiped us out.

21:45.847 --> 21:48.224
Our house ended up
a pile of splinters

21:48.224 --> 21:50.393
about a hundred yards
off the foundation.

21:50.393 --> 21:52.270
And my sister, um...

21:53.604 --> 21:55.690
...she was trying
to get to higher ground

21:55.690 --> 21:58.860
when a surge swept a car and
pinned her up against a bank.

21:58.860 --> 22:01.821
She was there for hours.
My mom lost

22:01.821 --> 22:03.990
her business,
the insurance company told us

22:03.990 --> 22:05.867
to file for bankruptcy, and...

22:05.867 --> 22:07.702
hospital bills.

22:07.702 --> 22:09.495
I’m sorry.

22:09.495 --> 22:10.538
[Dodge] Well, we were looking

22:10.538 --> 22:11.914
to move anyway.

22:11.914 --> 22:13.499
I told my mom

22:13.499 --> 22:15.460
that I needed to reenroll
in order to apply

22:15.460 --> 22:18.337
for a town service award.

22:18.337 --> 22:21.841
She thinks that I’m qualifying
hours this summer.

22:23.384 --> 22:25.678
You really are a good liar.

22:29.724 --> 22:31.350
But I trust you.

22:33.102 --> 22:35.313
And I think we’ll make
a good team.

22:35.313 --> 22:36.856
Team?

22:36.856 --> 22:38.399
[Natalie] Mm-hmm.

22:38.399 --> 22:39.734
I’ll help you win.

22:39.734 --> 22:41.486
We split the pot fifty-fifty.

22:41.486 --> 22:43.112
Look, I lived here all my life.

22:43.112 --> 22:45.698
I know the game. You don’t.

22:50.620 --> 22:51.954
What about Heather?

22:51.954 --> 22:53.081
What about her?

22:53.081 --> 22:55.083
Isn't she your best friend?

22:55.083 --> 22:56.834
Shouldn’t you be helping her?

22:57.877 --> 23:00.588
She swore to me
she’d never play.

23:00.588 --> 23:02.715
She said she couldn't even
watch me make the Jump.

23:02.715 --> 23:04.759
- She lied.
- You're angry at her
for playing.

23:04.759 --> 23:06.594
No.

23:06.594 --> 23:08.179
I’m angry at those 50 points.

23:09.680 --> 23:10.723
So...

23:12.183 --> 23:14.060
...we have a deal?

23:15.103 --> 23:16.854
It doesn’t really seem
like I have a choice.

23:16.854 --> 23:18.147
Mm-mm.

23:19.524 --> 23:21.109
What's that?

23:21.109 --> 23:23.111
Spurlock's farm.

23:24.112 --> 23:26.823
If we're gonna be partners...

23:26.823 --> 23:28.908
we're gonna have to come up
with a plan.

23:28.908 --> 23:30.910
Because there are
traps everywhere.

23:36.916 --> 23:38.918
[insects trilling]

23:43.756 --> 23:45.508
[Ray] Oh, my fucking God!

23:45.508 --> 23:47.718
Oh, my God, Lyons,
what the fuck, bro?

23:47.718 --> 23:49.720
- What?
- [laughing]

23:49.720 --> 23:51.806
Oh, my goodness.

23:51.806 --> 23:54.225
You know you're an actual
embarrassment, right?

23:54.225 --> 23:56.144
Can you please tell Lyons
he's an embarrassment?

23:56.144 --> 23:57.770
- No, he's your friend.
- He's not my friend.

23:57.770 --> 23:59.021
- Yeah, he's fucking
your friend.
-He's your friend!

23:59.021 --> 24:00.356
[Adam] Fuck you guys!

24:00.356 --> 24:01.649
Seriously,
when I strike it rich,

24:01.649 --> 24:03.442
you're not getting shit.

24:03.442 --> 24:05.528
What the hell?
Oh, my God, dude!

24:05.528 --> 24:07.613
You're giving me a fucking
headache with your bullshit.

24:07.613 --> 24:09.532
Tyler's always getting sensitive
when he's on his period.

24:09.532 --> 24:12.451
Ow! What the fuck, man?

24:12.451 --> 24:14.662
You know what, you've been in
a shitty mood all fucking day.

24:14.662 --> 24:16.622
You know what, I've been
in a shitty mood because we got

24:16.622 --> 24:17.874
busted at the second
challenge of the summer

24:17.874 --> 24:19.333
by the fucking cops!

24:21.794 --> 24:22.962
Now Miller's running her mouth.

24:22.962 --> 24:24.463
Yo! Miller knows
what she's doing.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.215
Well, maybe that explains
why she got arrested.

24:26.215 --> 24:28.009
Fuck's sake, let's just go.

24:28.009 --> 24:29.886
Fine.

24:29.886 --> 24:31.888
All right.

24:33.264 --> 24:34.807
Shit.

24:38.352 --> 24:40.354
[Tyler] I'm out!

24:41.898 --> 24:44.066
I'm fucking out.

24:44.066 --> 24:46.611
- What the fuck
you talking about?
- I said I'm out.

24:46.611 --> 24:47.945
I don't need the cops on my ass.

24:47.945 --> 24:49.363
- You're done with Panic?
- Yeah.

24:49.363 --> 24:50.531
Do I look like
I'm fucking joking?

24:50.531 --> 24:53.075
I'm clearing 800 bucks
a week, easy.

24:53.075 --> 24:54.118
So what?

24:54.118 --> 24:55.328
You're Steve Jobs now?

24:56.537 --> 24:58.456
You sell stolen pills
and shitty "H" to junkies...

24:58.456 --> 25:00.666
Hey, hey! My shit's clean.

25:00.666 --> 25:02.293
Before all the laxatives
and baby powder

25:02.293 --> 25:04.712
and fucking paint chips?

25:04.712 --> 25:06.172
Fuck you!

25:06.172 --> 25:08.257
Don't come crying to me for bail

25:08.257 --> 25:09.800
when Cortez shoves
your ass in jail!

25:09.800 --> 25:13.221
You're just jealous 'cause
I'm actually fucking earning.

25:13.221 --> 25:14.722
You know what?

25:14.722 --> 25:17.266
It's not worth it.

25:18.643 --> 25:19.936
You weren't gonna win anyway.

25:19.936 --> 25:21.896
You're too big of a pussy.

25:23.773 --> 25:25.274
Let's go.

25:29.403 --> 25:31.572
Hey, where do you think
you're going?

25:32.823 --> 25:35.952
[stammers] It's-it's
six miles to my house, man.

25:36.953 --> 25:39.080
Enjoy the walk.

25:39.080 --> 25:41.165
You shitting me?

25:41.165 --> 25:42.375
Guys!

25:42.375 --> 25:44.877
- [doors close]
- [engine starts]

25:44.877 --> 25:47.171
Ray! Ray, come on!

25:48.798 --> 25:51.008
Shit! Motherfucker!

26:15.574 --> 26:17.451
Bishop?

26:17.451 --> 26:21.956
You know, when you meet
someone around here,

26:21.956 --> 26:23.833
it's custom to say "Hello.

26:23.833 --> 26:25.751
How are you?"

26:27.753 --> 26:30.381
You going somewhere?

26:30.381 --> 26:33.259
Yeah, Heather's.

26:33.259 --> 26:35.469
Shouldn't be too long.

26:35.469 --> 26:37.513
Just gonna watch a movie.

26:37.513 --> 26:40.182
Had to sentence a boy last week.

26:40.182 --> 26:43.269
Took to breaking into houses
to pay for his kid’s diapers.

26:43.269 --> 26:47.273
Twelve months in detention
and another 12 months on parole.

26:47.273 --> 26:51.402
All for three minutes
of fun and a hangover.

26:51.402 --> 26:52.820
[chuckles]

26:52.820 --> 26:55.656
Yeah, yeah,
Heather’s just a friend.

26:55.656 --> 26:57.241
She's a pretty girl.

26:57.241 --> 26:58.951
Trust me.

26:58.951 --> 27:01.787
She won't seem like "just
a friend" for too much longer.

27:13.966 --> 27:15.968
♪ ♪

27:30.733 --> 27:32.234
Leela.

27:32.234 --> 27:34.612
Thanks for meeting me this late.

27:34.612 --> 27:36.614
I had to wait
for my parents to go to sleep.

27:36.614 --> 27:38.199
Don’t worry about it.

27:38.199 --> 27:40.701
This way.

27:48.834 --> 27:50.836
♪ ♪

28:15.236 --> 28:17.238
♪ ♪

28:27.373 --> 28:30.000
[Diggins] Time flies,
so fly like the crow

28:30.000 --> 28:33.504
To reap future treasures
from wars long ago

28:33.504 --> 28:36.382
Take one of these tokens
along when you leave

28:36.382 --> 28:38.634
And send proof in pictures
by midnight to me

28:38.634 --> 28:40.719
Ray, can you please stop that?

28:40.719 --> 28:43.639
[Troy] Um, translation...

28:43.639 --> 28:47.017
- please?
- Troy, I wish
that I could help you.

28:47.017 --> 28:49.478
- But the puzzle is part of...
- You’re supposed
to steal something.

28:49.478 --> 28:51.772
- [Diggins] Thank you, Summer.
- [Summer] Uh, okay.

28:51.772 --> 28:54.442
Uh, so we have to go
in-inside the house?

28:54.442 --> 28:56.360
Illegal entry...
it happens every year.

28:56.360 --> 28:58.904
- Hmm, student
becomes the master?
- [Diggins] You can choose

28:58.904 --> 29:01.240
the cornfields or the woods
to get to Spurlock's.

29:01.240 --> 29:03.367
And 'cause we didn't
complete the last challenge,

29:03.367 --> 29:07.163
the judges decided it was unfair
to award or deduct any points

29:07.163 --> 29:08.581
- based...
- Wait, how is that fair?

29:09.957 --> 29:12.168
- Some of us actually
had to cross.
- Yeah, not all of us.

29:12.168 --> 29:13.794
- Yeah, I had to cross, Diggins.
- Yeah, man, yeah.

29:13.794 --> 29:15.921
Rankings are the same as they
were after the first challenge.

29:15.921 --> 29:17.631
Also, 'cause the cops busted us,

29:17.631 --> 29:19.633
no more spectators.

29:19.633 --> 29:21.510
We're still missing Tyler.

29:21.510 --> 29:23.929
He'll be here.

29:23.929 --> 29:25.431
[Summer] Okay, we'll just
sneak in, steal something,

29:25.431 --> 29:27.683
get out, and then take a picture

29:27.683 --> 29:29.143
and send proof to Diggins
by midnight.

29:29.143 --> 29:32.605
This challenge is worth
50 points, all or nothing.

29:32.605 --> 29:35.316
You need 150 in order to make it
to the next challenge, so...

29:35.316 --> 29:36.609
give it all you got.

29:36.609 --> 29:38.486
[laughter]

29:38.486 --> 29:40.112
Good luck.

29:40.112 --> 29:42.114
And Spurlock's a nutcase.

29:42.114 --> 29:44.867
Like, supposedly the whole place
is booby-trapped,

29:44.867 --> 29:46.827
so just try not to die.

29:46.827 --> 29:48.537
♪ ♪

29:52.166 --> 29:54.376
[Natalie] Okay, let's do this.

29:54.376 --> 29:55.753
[laughter]

29:55.753 --> 29:58.005
- [indistinct chatter]
- [whooping]

29:58.005 --> 29:59.381
You ready?

29:59.381 --> 30:01.675
- Yeah.
- Let's go around the woods.

30:01.675 --> 30:03.719
[♪ Algiers: "There Is No Year"]

30:03.719 --> 30:06.347
♪ This self-consuming
contradiction ♪

30:08.140 --> 30:12.186
♪ The more it turns,
the more we just deform ♪

30:13.854 --> 30:18.734
♪ But either way, you can't
look in my dark room ♪

30:18.734 --> 30:21.111
♪ With new words
for God and country ♪

30:21.111 --> 30:24.323
♪ New words
for every song we sing ♪

30:24.323 --> 30:27.618
♪ Whoa... ♪

30:27.618 --> 30:30.204
♪ And it's only
to get shot down ♪

30:30.204 --> 30:32.289
♪ Whoa... ♪

30:32.289 --> 30:34.166
♪ It's only to get...

30:34.166 --> 30:36.168
- [animal screeching]
- Stop!

30:43.425 --> 30:45.803
- Gross.
- Yeah.

30:47.555 --> 30:49.557
♪ Whoa... ♪

30:51.016 --> 30:53.644
♪ It's only to get
shot down...

30:53.644 --> 30:56.730
[muttering] Oh, shit!

30:56.730 --> 30:58.482
♪ It's only to get shot down ♪

30:58.482 --> 31:00.651
♪ Whoa... ♪

31:00.651 --> 31:03.195
♪ It's only to get shot ♪♪

31:03.195 --> 31:07.074
- Okay, so which way now?
- [Natalie] Um...

31:07.074 --> 31:09.368
it'll be faster
if we split up and scout.

31:09.368 --> 31:11.370
Um, we should see
the greenhouses soon,

31:11.370 --> 31:13.747
or we're too far west.

31:13.747 --> 31:16.000
Let's meet back at
the next break in ten minutes?

31:16.000 --> 31:17.042
Got it.

31:17.042 --> 31:19.128
Hey, watch out.

31:19.128 --> 31:21.380
Okay.

31:21.380 --> 31:23.382
[insects trilling]

31:46.864 --> 31:48.407
[Dodge] Nicely done.

31:48.407 --> 31:50.200
Very, uh, convincing.

31:50.200 --> 31:52.161
- Where'd you learn how to lie?
- See, it isn't a lie

31:52.161 --> 31:54.204
as long as you believe
the story you tell.

31:54.204 --> 31:55.831
But you already know that,
don’t you?

31:56.874 --> 31:58.125
Right. Come on.

31:58.125 --> 31:59.627
We’re wasting time.

32:07.676 --> 32:10.804
[chuckles] Nice try, Spurlock.

32:12.097 --> 32:14.099
Go fuck yourself.

32:15.267 --> 32:17.102
[panting]

32:19.104 --> 32:20.314
[yelps]

32:22.191 --> 32:24.068
Fuck me.

32:24.068 --> 32:26.070
[coughing]

32:28.489 --> 32:30.908
What the fuck?

32:38.791 --> 32:40.000
Natalie?

32:41.502 --> 32:43.128
Natalie.

32:46.840 --> 32:48.842
[crunching]

32:48.842 --> 32:50.928
[panting]

32:50.928 --> 32:52.137
[creature chittering]

32:52.137 --> 32:53.722
What the fuck?

32:56.058 --> 32:58.268
Damn it.

32:59.728 --> 33:01.313
[Natalie] Remember the plan.

33:01.313 --> 33:03.899
We should have decent coverage
of the house from the woods.

33:03.899 --> 33:06.193
Scope out all the entrances.

33:06.193 --> 33:08.112
Uh, I'll keep eye
on the front door.

33:08.112 --> 33:10.447
- You took photos of the map?
- Yeah.

33:10.447 --> 33:12.908
- Okay.
- All right. Wish me luck.

33:12.908 --> 33:15.911
Hey. Be careful.

33:25.212 --> 33:26.588
[girl] Is this right?

33:27.840 --> 33:29.550
Yeah. It's right here.

33:35.514 --> 33:37.641
Guys, over here.

33:40.060 --> 33:41.770
Come on.
We're running out of time.

33:41.770 --> 33:43.355
Let's go. Come on, come on.

33:48.318 --> 33:49.862
[screams]

33:49.862 --> 33:50.946
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

33:50.946 --> 33:52.865
- Are you okay?
- Shawna, help me.

33:52.865 --> 33:53.991
[Shawna] It's okay.
I'm gonna get you out.

33:53.991 --> 33:55.367
Okay? Just give me one second.

33:59.997 --> 34:01.623
[whistling]

34:16.096 --> 34:18.098
[whistling stops]

34:22.603 --> 34:23.812
[grunts softly]

34:27.441 --> 34:28.817
Little help?

34:35.741 --> 34:37.951
Yeah. Come on.

34:39.369 --> 34:41.872
Here. Give me that.

34:49.797 --> 34:51.465
Thanks.

35:00.390 --> 35:02.476
[Ray] Well, well, well,
if it isn't Nill on her knees.

35:05.062 --> 35:06.647
[exhales]

35:06.647 --> 35:08.941
Looking for something?

35:08.941 --> 35:10.776
Yeah, my phone.

35:10.776 --> 35:13.529
Ah, your phone.

35:13.529 --> 35:14.988
[mutters] Let me see if I can...

35:15.989 --> 35:17.241
Sorry.

35:24.414 --> 35:26.124
Shit.

35:27.167 --> 35:28.794
Thanks.

35:28.794 --> 35:30.796
You’re going the wrong way,
you know.

35:32.923 --> 35:34.925
The house is south
of the cornfield.

35:34.925 --> 35:36.927
You sure you’re going south?

35:38.303 --> 35:39.930
You’re fucking with me.

35:39.930 --> 35:43.809
I know a shortcut,
if you want to follow me.

35:44.810 --> 35:47.312
Thank you, but I’ll pass.

35:47.312 --> 35:48.856
What? Don’t trust me?

35:48.856 --> 35:50.732
No. Why would I?

35:50.732 --> 35:53.443
You tried to sabotage Dodge
at the last challenge.

35:53.443 --> 35:55.404
I don’t need sabotage to win,
sweetheart.

35:57.573 --> 36:00.158
Time’s a-ticking.

36:00.158 --> 36:01.785
[tongue clicking]

36:01.785 --> 36:03.954
Yeah, I don't want
to point out the obvious,

36:03.954 --> 36:06.790
but I’m actually
the one that's winning.

36:06.790 --> 36:09.918
You were winning.
Now you’re lost.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.922
I'm willing to lend you
a helping hand.

36:15.674 --> 36:20.220
You knows? Maybe you’ll even
return the favor.

36:24.892 --> 36:26.894
I’d rather fucking die.

36:40.908 --> 36:42.534
[grunts]

36:54.588 --> 36:56.214
Ray?

36:57.215 --> 36:59.217
[device clicking]

37:08.894 --> 37:10.896
[Adam] Grow house.

37:23.909 --> 37:25.911
[gasps]

37:28.121 --> 37:30.123
Sick.

37:33.335 --> 37:34.836
[grunts]

37:36.922 --> 37:39.049
[exhales] Show me the money.

37:52.145 --> 37:54.439
[quietly] Fuck.

37:54.439 --> 37:56.984
[device clicking]

38:05.158 --> 38:06.368
[device whirring]

38:07.536 --> 38:09.579
[alarms blaring]

38:13.000 --> 38:14.209
[alarms stop]

38:16.420 --> 38:18.380
[Spurlock] Son of a bitch.
Fucking kidding me.

38:18.380 --> 38:21.967
You got ten seconds
to clear off my land!

38:21.967 --> 38:24.261
- Ten. Nine.
- Fuck.

38:24.261 --> 38:26.179
Oh, fuck.

38:26.179 --> 38:29.725
Eight. Seven.

38:29.725 --> 38:31.727
- [gunshot]
- Six.

38:31.727 --> 38:33.061
[gunshot]

38:35.897 --> 38:38.900
Five seconds
before I start aiming.

38:48.827 --> 38:51.913
Fuck it. Pretty sure
I just lost count.

38:51.913 --> 38:53.999
[racks shotgun]

38:57.210 --> 38:58.420
[gunshot]

39:01.923 --> 39:03.175
I'm coming for you!

39:04.217 --> 39:05.594
[gunshot]

39:29.076 --> 39:31.495
- [tires screech]
- Huh?

39:31.495 --> 39:33.497
What the... what the fuck?

39:34.498 --> 39:36.500
- [gunshot]
- [Spurlock shouting
indistinctly]

39:36.500 --> 39:39.002
[twig snaps]

39:39.002 --> 39:41.004
[footsteps approaching]

39:43.965 --> 39:45.133
[gunshot]

39:46.843 --> 39:48.428
Hey, man.

39:50.597 --> 39:52.057
Stop! No, no, no!

39:52.057 --> 39:54.392
Stop! What the fuck?
What the fuck?

39:54.392 --> 39:56.978
Let go! Fuck!

39:56.978 --> 39:58.563
Let go of me! Fuck!

39:58.563 --> 40:01.191
Let go! What the fuck
are you guys...

40:01.191 --> 40:03.276
[shouts]

40:03.276 --> 40:05.987
No, wait, wait, wait. Fuck!

40:05.987 --> 40:09.241
- What the fuck do you want?
- [muffled pounding]

40:09.241 --> 40:12.410
Fuck! Let me out!

40:21.336 --> 40:23.338
[footsteps approaching]

40:27.843 --> 40:29.845
[metal clinking]

40:32.514 --> 40:34.516
Hello?

40:38.186 --> 40:40.480
Hello?

40:40.480 --> 40:44.109
Hello? Come on,
somebody help me!

40:50.157 --> 40:55.579
♪ You can't talk to me,
I'm in my zone ♪

40:57.706 --> 41:02.252
♪ I do what I want
with what I own ♪

41:02.252 --> 41:05.255
♪ Own, own, own ♪

41:05.255 --> 41:10.051
♪ Don't preach to the queen
about her throne ♪

41:12.470 --> 41:17.601
♪ The time for being nice
is dead and gone ♪

41:17.601 --> 41:20.187
♪ Gone, gone, gone ♪

41:20.187 --> 41:23.982
♪ You took a knife,
ran it right through me ♪

41:23.982 --> 41:25.650
♪ Twisted and twisted
and twisted it ♪

41:25.650 --> 41:27.861
♪ Until it consumed me ♪

41:27.861 --> 41:31.656
♪ You made a mess,
I picked up the pieces ♪

41:31.656 --> 41:34.451
♪ Thanks, it was all
for a reason ♪

41:34.451 --> 41:36.912
♪ Just look at me now ♪

41:36.912 --> 41:40.665
♪ Look at me now-ow-ow-ow ♪

41:40.665 --> 41:44.669
♪ Just look at me now-ow-ow-ow ♪

41:44.669 --> 41:47.964
♪ Look at me now-ow-ow-ow ♪

41:47.964 --> 41:51.343
♪ Just look at me now-ow-ow-ow ♪

41:51.343 --> 41:52.886
♪ Just look at me now ♪

41:52.886 --> 41:57.641
♪ I don't really think much
of your style ♪

41:57.641 --> 41:59.935
♪ Ha, ha ♪

41:59.935 --> 42:04.606
♪ Get a grip,
I think you're in denial ♪

42:04.606 --> 42:07.651
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

42:07.651 --> 42:12.364
♪ I can see the snake
behind your smile ♪

42:15.158 --> 42:20.121
♪ But I'm not a prey
you can devour ♪

42:20.121 --> 42:22.749
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪♪

42:22.749 --> 42:24.751
♪ ♪
